HEADWORD: Erythema
<hw>Er`y*the"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/, fr. <?/ to redden, fr. <grk>'eryqro`s</grk> red.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disease of the skin, in which a diffused
inflammation forms rose-colored patches of variable size.</def>⟦br⟧
